  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN171-kilavi">talaimakaṉ piriviṉkaṇ vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaḷait tōḻi <app><lem>vaṟpuṟuttiyatu</lem><rdg wit="#RK">vaṟpuṟīiyatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante consoled HER who had undergone changes during the separation from HIM.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN171">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>nutalu nuṇpacap <supplied>pi</supplied>varun tōḷu</l>
        <l>makaṉmalai yiṟumpi ṉāyntukoṇ ṭaṟutta</l>
        <l>paṇaiyeḻi laḻiya vāṭu nāḷu</l>
        <l>niṉaivaṉ mātavar paṇpaṉ ṟōvā</l>
        <l>tiṉaiyal vāḻi tōḻi puṇarva</l>
        <l>rilaṅkukō lāytoṭi nekiḻap poruḷpurin</l>
        <l>talantalai ñemaiyat tataraṭain tirunta</l>
        <l>mālvaraic cīṟūr maruḷpaṉ mākkaḷ</l>
        <l>kōḷva lēṟṟai yōcai yōrmār</l>
        <l>tiruttik koṇṭa vampiṉar nōṉcilai</l>
        <l>yeruttat tirīi yiṭantoṟum paṭartaliṟ</l>
        <l>kīḻppaṭut tāra muṇṇā mēṟciṉaip</l>
        <l>paḻampōl cēṟṟa tīmpuṉa luṇīiya</l>
        <l>karuṅkōṭ ṭiruppai yūrum</l>
        <l>peruṅkai yeṇkiṉ curaṉiṟan tōrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>“Fine pallor creeps over [my] forehead and [my] shoulders (1)</l>
        <l>fade so that [their] grace of bamboo, hand-picked and cut</l>
        <l>from the thicket on the vast mountain, perishes. Do I not</l>
        <l>daily think [so]? This is not like him. Without stopping [such talk], (2-4)</l>
        <l>do not despair, oh friend. He will join [us], (5)</l>
        <l>the one who, desiring wealth so that [your] shining beautiful choice bangles become loose, (6)</l>
        <l>has gone to traverse the desert of big-pawed bears (15)</l>
        <l>that climb Mahua trees with black branches (14)</l>
        <l>in order to drink the muddy sweet flood that is fruitlike (13)</l>
        <l>from the upper twigs, without eating the edibles that lie below, (12)</l>
        <l>because the many confused people from the little villages by the vast mountains, (8)</l>
        <l>who sit close to the road with Ñemai trees whose heads have suffered, (7)</l>
        <l>set out to every [such] place, putting on napes [of their necks] (11)</l>
        <l>sturdy bows, people with finely honed arrows, (10)</l>
        <l>in order to listen for the sound of the males strong in killing. (9)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

